{"info": {"author": "Mike Phillipson", "author_email": "MICHAEL_PHILLIPSON1@homedepot.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# cryptofy\n\nSimple encryption/decryption functions for Python\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install cryptofy\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n**Generate** a secret:\n\n```python\nfrom cryptofy import encoding, generate_secret\n\nkey = generate_secret().decode(encoding)\n\nprint(key)  # Output randomized secret\n```\n\n**Encrypt** a string:\n\n```python\nfrom cryptofy import encoding, encrypt\n\nstring = \"my-password\"\nkey = \"my-secret\"\n\nencrypted = encrypt(bytes(key, encoding=encoding), bytes(string, encoding))\n\nprint(encrypted)  # Output ciphertext\n```\n\n**Decrypt** ciphertext:\n\n```python\nfrom cryptofy import encoding, decrypt\n\nencrypted = \"<ciphertext>\"\nkey = \"my-secret\"\n\nstring = decrypt(bytes(key, encoding=encoding), encrypted).decode(encoding)\n\nprint(string)  # Output decrypted string\n```\n\n## Command Line\n\n### Usage:\n\n```\ncryptofy ((-d | -e) -k <key> -s <source>) | (-n [-l <length>])\n```\n\n**Example 1:** Generate a secret\n\n```\ncryptofy -n\n```\n\n**Example 2:** Encrypt a string:\n\n```\ncryptofy -e -k \"my-secret\" -s \"my-password\"\n```\n\n**Example 3:** Decrypt ciphertext:\n\n```\ncryptofy -d -k \"my-secret\" -s \"<ciphertext>\"\n```\n\n## License\n\nDistributed under the [Apache, version 2.0 license](https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0).", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/homedepot/cryptofy", "keywords": "", "license": "Apache 2.0", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "cryptofy", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cryptofy/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cryptofy/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/homedepot/cryptofy"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cryptofy/1.1.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Simple encryption/decryption functions for Python", "version": "1.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>cryptofy</h1>\n<p>Simple encryption/decryption functions for Python</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre><code>pip install cryptofy\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p><strong>Generate</strong> a secret:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">cryptofy</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">generate_secret</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">key</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">generate_secret</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># Output randomized secret</span>\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Encrypt</strong> a string:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">cryptofy</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">encrypt</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">string</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"my-password\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">key</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"my-secret\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">encrypted</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">encrypt</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">bytes</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">),</span> <span class=\"nb\">bytes</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">string</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">encrypted</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># Output ciphertext</span>\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Decrypt</strong> ciphertext:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">cryptofy</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">decrypt</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">encrypted</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"&lt;ciphertext&gt;\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">key</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"my-secret\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">string</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">decrypt</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">bytes</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">),</span> <span class=\"n\">encrypted</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">string</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># Output decrypted string</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Command Line</h2>\n<h3>Usage:</h3>\n<pre><code>cryptofy ((-d | -e) -k &lt;key&gt; -s &lt;source&gt;) | (-n [-l &lt;length&gt;])\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Example 1:</strong> Generate a secret</p>\n<pre><code>cryptofy -n\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Example 2:</strong> Encrypt a string:</p>\n<pre><code>cryptofy -e -k \"my-secret\" -s \"my-password\"\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Example 3:</strong> Decrypt ciphertext:</p>\n<pre><code>cryptofy -d -k \"my-secret\" -s \"&lt;ciphertext&gt;\"\n</code></pre>\n<h2>License</h2>\n<p>Distributed under the <a href=\"https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apache, version 2.0 license</a>.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7087033, "releases": {"1.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "74feac82be69204a2832776d6f6f11ac", "sha256": "9f140c649b86744198ebe231e0cb7076a36786b08a784fb650908356e80faf35"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cryptofy-1.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "74feac82be69204a2832776d6f6f11ac", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 6796, "upload_time": "2020-03-13T00:59:50", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-13T00:59:50.810784Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/d2/9a/a5b0601f6f1fea53e0985d71763c8768a8c5e81c25701e73487339092878/cryptofy-1.0.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "67a797753050348df76473566ee20dca", "sha256": "6d1c03957bd9c98654158d305fc5ce521562606c2bc30ab5106f724cd7fc3a7f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cryptofy-1.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "67a797753050348df76473566ee20dca", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 6816, "upload_time": "2020-04-14T22:00:57", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-14T22:00:57.551487Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7d/1d/c9a9380a4e8e426831e2b4a5f1e8291ac4c0eef31786ba3ba40c6b079d04/cryptofy-1.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}]}, "urls": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "67a797753050348df76473566ee20dca", "sha256": "6d1c03957bd9c98654158d305fc5ce521562606c2bc30ab5106f724cd7fc3a7f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cryptofy-1.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "67a797753050348df76473566ee20dca", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 6816, "upload_time": "2020-04-14T22:00:57", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-14T22:00:57.551487Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7d/1d/c9a9380a4e8e426831e2b4a5f1e8291ac4c0eef31786ba3ba40c6b079d04/cryptofy-1.1